Introduction

(G)I-DLE is a South Korean multi-national girl group under Cube Entertainment. The group consists of five members: Miyeon, Minnie, Soyeon, Yuqi, and Shuhua. (G)I-DLE debuted on May 2nd, 2018 with their debut mini-album "I am", and "LATATA" serving as the title track.

The group debuted with six members, but on August 14, 2021, Cube Entertainment announced Soojin’s departure. The agency apologized for the controversy involving their artist Soojin, who had been on hiatus since March due to accusations of bullying her schoolmates.

Following Soojin's departure in August 2021, (G)I-DLE returned as a five-member group with their first studio album “I Never Die” on March 14, 2022.

On November 30, 2024, during the Melon Music Awards, Soyeon announced in their Record of the Year (Daesang) acceptance speech that all five members had decided to renew their contracts with Cube Entertainment just before arriving at the ceremony.
